# Deliverables Table Template

The deliverables table is the most-scrutinized part of §4 Project Scope. Operators read this first; clients read this second. Get it specific.

## Format

| Deliverable | Description | Estimated Time |
|---|---|---|
| <short name> | <one-line specific description with stream/unit refs> | <X> days |

## Common deliverable rows by service line

Copy the rows that apply, then customize. Don't ship the template names verbatim — each row should reference the client's specific units/streams.

### Performance studies (most common)

| Deliverable | Description | Time |
|---|---|---|
| Pre-test meeting + Data Request Sheet | Align on test plan with {{CLIENT}} operations + engineering. DCS data inventory check. | 2 days |
| Onsite sampling campaign | Sample acid gas at {{AG_STREAMS}}, tail gas at {{TG_STREAMS}}, condensate analysis where applicable. {{N}} runs over {{D}} days. | {{D}} days |
| Symmetry™ process model | Calibrated against {{N}} samples and {{D}} days of DCS data. Sensitivity analysis on key variables. | 10 days |
| Performance assessment report | Identifies bottlenecks, quantifies efficiency gap to design, recommends action items ranked by ROI. | 15 days |
| Close-out call + Q&A | 90-min web meeting with {{CLIENT}} team to walk through findings + recommendations. | 1 day |

