## Estimation rules of thumb

These are not in the proposal — they're for the drafter to calibrate estimates.

- **Pre-test work + Data Request Sheet**: minimum 2 days regardless of project size
- **Onsite sampling**: 1 day per RF/condenser pair tested, minimum 4 onsite days for travel justification
- **Symmetry model build**: 5 days for re-tune of existing model; 10-15 days for new model build
- **Performance report**: 1-2 days per recommendation item · typical 5-8 recommendations → 10-15 days
- **Training course delivery**: classroom-day = 1 SRE engineer-day; plant walkdown adds 0.5 days
- **Tender response**: 5-10 days depending on complexity; bid bond docs add 2 days
- **HAZOP support**: 1 day prep per HAZOP day attended
- **Conceptual design**: 4-6 weeks engineering time
- **Basic engineering**: 8-12 weeks engineering time (parallel to procurement)

When in doubt, **estimate high and offer to discuss**. Underestimating is worse than overestimating — it leads to overtime invoices, late deliveries, and client dissatisfaction.

